{
  "_meta": {
    "title": "Helix Thready — Figma Variables (canonical token set)",
    "classification": "PUBLIC",
    "location": "docs/public/research/mvp/design/figma/figma-variables.json",
    "status": "Draft — v0.1",
    "revision": "1 (2026-07-22)",
    "author": "Helix Thready documentation swarm (design · figma)",
    "source_of_truth": "../opendesign/tokens.css — every hex value is carried verbatim; r/g/b floats are hex/255 rounded to 6 decimals; nothing is invented [CONSTITUTION 11.4.6]",
    "format": "Figma Variables REST API bulk-change shape (POST /v1/files/{file_key}/variables) with temporary ids; the same structure maps 1:1 onto the Plugin API (figma.variables.createVariableCollection / createVariable / setValueForMode / addMode)",
    "consumption_notes": [
      "Keys prefixed with '_' (this _meta block and per-entry _hex comments) are documentation only — strip them before POSTing: jq 'del(._meta) | walk(if type == \"object\" then del(._hex) else . end)'",
      "The REST endpoint requires an Enterprise-plan token; on any other plan, replay the same structure through the Plugin API (Figma MCP `use_figma`) or a variables-import plugin — see ./README.md.",
      "ds-heart is a VARIABLE_ALIAS to accent in both modes, mirroring tokens.css `--ds-heart: var(--accent)`.",
      "NOT carried as variables (by design, documented in figma-file-plan.md section 4): B-slot aliases fg-2/meta/border-soft (pure aliases), accent-hover/accent-active and elev-raised/focus-ring (CSS color-mix() formulas — baked into component styles per mode), ease-standard (cubic bezier, prototype setting), section rhythm + gutters (frame layout annotations), font families (Figma text styles, not variables), tracking-display (text styles)."
    ]
  },
